This study proposed a research framework for the sustainable development of localized cities aligned with SDGs (Fig. 2
                           ). The construction of a localized urban scale indicator system for SDGs incorporated both top-down and bottom-up approaches. First, we interpreted the framework of the 17 first-level goals and 169 second-level goals of the SDGs, and assessed the usability of 231 specific sustainable development indicators, selecting those that could be directly adopted. Then, we supplemented indicators from the existing database that fit the SDGs connotation and region development characteristics, to form a localized sustainable development assessment indicator system (Table 1
                           ). Among them, SDG 14 on marine resources is not included because the study area includes inland cities. Additionally, SDGs 5, 16, and 17 are not included in the evaluation system due to the lack of quantitative indicators.
